10-15 mins before ready to serve, halve, peel and thinly slice the @shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Put a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat and add the @butter{30}g.

Allow it to melt, then add the shallot and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}, stirring.

Add the garlic and stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Then add @peas{360}g and cook, stirring, until piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Squeeze in a little @lemon{1/2}(juiced), season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and remove from the heat.

Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

> Green garden peas are a vibrant addition to any dish, and this recipe sees them sauteed with plenty of butter to make it a truly special side. Fried gently with shallot, garlic and a dash of lemon juice, these are anything but ordinary peas.